No business can be all things to all people.
 Saint Laurie Merchant Tailors is no exception.
 Not everyone likes the same movies, music or art.
 There’s no reason everyone should like the same clothier.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Crafting custom suits in NYC by Saint LaurieWhat our clients have in common
 is not simply their professions or wealth.
 Nor do we appeal to a narrow age group.
 You’d probably be surprised at the range of ages, income levels, jobs and
 places of residence of our clients.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, they do have something very important in common.
 They are all “thinking men” and their approach to shopping is distinctive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The “thinking man”…
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
…
\emph on
\color blue
does not make purchasing decisions solely on the basis of price.
 He doesn’t assume that the most expensive is the best or that the cheapest
 is a bargain.
 He seeks value in his purchases, which requires a thoughtful cost/benefit
 analysis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
…
\emph on
\color blue
does not rely on brand names or labels as the sole criteria for establishing
 the merits of a product.
 Instead, he wants to make an intelligent decision and soaks up relevant
 information like a sponge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
…values expertise.
 He takes pride in an address book filled with experts to help him succeed
 in life.
 His trust has to be earned, but once it is, he is extremely loyal.
 And he understands the unforeseen detours involved in making custom clothing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
…understands that dressing is an important form of nonverbal communication.
 He sees it as an advantage to take pride in the way he looks.
 He is also considerate of others by dressing appropriately for every occasion.
\end_layout

